avalan for Debian
=================

This package installs the Avalan SDK and the `avalan` / `avl`
command-line tools without pulling in heavyweight or
hardware-specific dependencies. A few features need extra setup,
described below.

Out-of-scope extras
-------------------

The .deb ships the upstream `agent`, `server`, `tool`, and `vendors`
extras. The following upstream extras are not in the .deb:

  * `a2a`           — Google's Agent2Agent SDK
  * `browser`       — Playwright (web automation / scraping)
  * `code`          — RestrictedPython sandbox
  * `youtube`       — youtube-transcript-api
  * `litellm`       — LiteLLM multi-provider router
  * `local`         — torch + transformers + huggingface-hub
  * `vision`        — diffusers + opencv + torchvision
  * `audio`         — soundfile + torchaudio
  * `memory`        — vector stores + tree-sitter + pdf tooling
  * `mlx` / `apple` — Apple-silicon MLX runtime
  * `nvidia` / `vllm` / `quantization`
                    — CUDA + vLLM + bitsandbytes
  * `ds4`           — DualShock 4 input
  * `secrets`       — boto3 + keyring
  * `translation`   — protobuf + sentencepiece

To use any of them, create a virtualenv and install with pip on top
of the system Avalan install:

    python3 -m venv ~/.avalan/venv
    source ~/.avalan/venv/bin/activate
    pip install "avalan[browser]"      # or [code], [youtube], [local], ...

The system `avalan` and `avl` keep working alongside the venv; the
venv-installed copy shadows them only while activated.

Playwright browsers
-------------------

If you opt into the `browser` extra above, Playwright itself does not
bundle a browser. Pick one of:

  1. System browser (recommended on shared hosts):

       sudo apt install chromium      # or: sudo apt install firefox

     then set `PLAYWRIGHT_BROWSERS_PATH=/usr/bin` and pass the system
     executable via Playwright's `executable_path` API.

  2. Playwright-managed browsers (per-user):

       playwright install

     binaries land under `~/.cache/ms-playwright/`.

The .deb itself never fetches a browser; this step is opt-in.

API keys
--------

Vendor backends (OpenAI, Anthropic, Google, AWS) read their
credentials from environment variables at runtime. The package does
not configure them — set them in your shell, .env, systemd unit, or
secret store as appropriate.

